== Beginning Rails Source Code and Sample Application

* The Rails installation script for OS X 10.4.x (Chapter 2, pages 27-28) can
  be found in install_rails_osx.sh.

* The source code for the entire event management application can be found in
  the events directory.


== Installation of the events application

* Make sure you have Ruby, Rails, and MySql installed
* Copy the events directory to a location on your computer and change into
  that directory
* Create two new MySql databases: events_development and events_test
* Copy the database config file from config/database.yml.tpl to config/database.yml and
  customize it for the databases you just created
* Initialize the database using `rake db:schema:load` from the command line
* Start the web server using `./script/server`


Please report any and all errata to the authors at http://beginningrails.com

